    <description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Rashere wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;The new quest system is&amp;nbsp;a global system and will be available&#xD;
on the server.&amp;nbsp; What we're limiting are which specific quests are&#xD;
available.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;p&gt;Rashere&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;I loathe and detest the new quest&#xD;
system. The original EQ quest system was very simple and easy to&#xD;
follow. The new one is obfuscatory and nitpickingly fiddly to use.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I am certainly not against the use of in-game quest journals that&#xD;
automatically record and update your quests for you - EQ2 has an&#xD;
excellent system like that. I am just opposed to the irritating,&#xD;
confusing annoying version of the concept which has been crowbarred&#xD;
into EQ.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
The net result for me of the quest system being added was that I added&#xD;
quests to tasks as being too intrusive to smooth gameplay to be worth&#xD;
the hassle.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I can't see how the new system can be considered clearer or easier than&#xD;
just talking to an NPC and reading their reply in your text window,&#xD;
which to my mind was about the simplest possible way of delivering&#xD;
quest content.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
